Detailed Description

Fundamental class to store the dynamical information for one body.

jrlCIRdynamicsJRLJapan::DynamicBody::MAL_S3_VECTOR ( double   ) 

Here are the physical parameters (as defined in Kajita's book page 46 figure 2.20):

  • a = rotation vector,
  • b = translation vector,
  • c = center of mass,
  • w_c = center of mass in reference frame,
  • p = position,
  • v0 = linear velocity in reference frame,
  • dv = linear acceleration,
  • w = angular velocity,
  • dw = angular acceleration,
  • sv, sw = spatial velocity,
  • cv, cw = cross velocity term,
  • pph, ppb = v x Iv
